The Health Department has recorded 1 742 new COVID-19 cases, pushing the number of total infections to 1 479 253. There have been a further 396 COVID-19 related deaths in the country, bringing the national death toll to 46 869. In a statement, Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize says most of the new deaths were recorded in Limpopo. “Regrettably, we report 396 more COVID-19 related deaths: 20 from Eastern Cape, 6 from the Free State, 81 from Gauteng, 85 from KwaZulu-Natal, 118 from Limpopo, 18 from Mpumalanga, 3 from the Northern Cape and 65 from the Western Cape,” says Dr Mkhize. The total number of recoveries stands at 1 367 247. The cumulative total number of tests conducted to date is 8 538 269.  396 1 742 1 479 253 8 538 269 65 137 46 869 1 367 247 *As at 9 February 2021 1 414 116 (function(d){var js, id="pikto-embed-js", ref=d.getElementsByTagName("script")[0];if (d.getElementById(id)) { return;}js=d.createElement("script"); js.id=id; js.async=true;js.src="https://create.piktochart.com/assets/embedding/embed.js";ref.parentNode.insertBefore(js, ref);}(document)); 